snippet.textDisplay:
120fps / 8K my  ugly hairy butt, it's just "up to", not the standard experience.. reality will be this:
2020:  Games run native 4K at 60 fps (High Preset),  Shooters will go up to 120 fps at 1080p (High Preset)
2022:  Games run 1800p at 60 fps (Medium Preset),  some Shooters at 100 fps at 1080p (Medium Preset)
2024:  "Xbone Scarlet X" will run games at native 4K at 60 fps (Ultra Preset),  some shooters at 120 fps at 1080 (Ultra Preset)

Cause you know.. games go harder on requirements every year, so don't expect to get stable performance (60fps/Ntive 4K) as the standers experience
Sacrificing Native resolution (checkerboard rendering) or sacrifice the PRESET, either ways, there is some sacrifices to get 60 fps at 4K in the long run
